name: Delirium Canyon
description:
Introduction

A hidden gem in the remote sycamore wilderness. This route is located off a gated road. Mountain bikes, e-bikes, atv's, and OHV less than 4 feet wide can access the road. Utilizing these resources could eliminate the 3.7 miles each way of bumpy road walking. The sneak exit is brushy and steep but makes this route doable in a day.

Due to the remote nature and keeper pothole this route is only reccomended for experienced canyoneers craving a long adventure in a rugged and pristine wilderness.

The R rating is for the keeper pothole and remote location.

Retrievable anchors used on 4 out of 6 rappels. Bring webbing.

Approach

Start at Taylor cabin th and take the casner mtn road to the head of the canyon.

Descent

R1. Rabbit Hole. 60' off pinch LDC. Through hole down chute. CAUTION! False floor near edge.

R2. KEEPER. 100' Fiddle off tree RDC. Down chute 60 to keeper pothole. Avoidable via LDC traverse on ledge to Lip. Or 60 to pothole and 40' downclimb.

R3. Downclimb to first ledge. 40' Fiddle off tree RDC.

R4 30' Fiddle tree RDC.

R5. BIG DROP 200' off tree RDC to first ledge . Or 235' to the bottom

R6. 25' fiddle off sapling RDC ( To bottom of big drop).

After the big drop you can gear down. A few small downclimbs to negotiate before reaching the exit.

Supai narrows

Exit

Follow sneak exit back up to your bikes and the main rd.

The longer alternate exit allows for an overnight at Taylor cabin.

Red tape

Beta sites

Trip reports and media

Background

Discovered on June 6, 2022 by Bogan Lawrence, Kevin Iosue and Eric Moorcroft.

properties.description: Starting at the technical section up to 6 rappels 200' max

properties.name: Exit
properties.description: Gane the ridge and navigate through brushy terrain. Protective layers reccomended.

properties.name: Approach
properties.description:
This road is gated and has big hills , and loose gravel. 

Bikes optional approx 1 hr. 
On foot approach  2 hours.

properties.name: Parking
properties.description: Space limited. Up to two cars. Do not block the gate!!!!

properties.name: Big drop
properties.description: 200' to first ledge. Then 35' off a tree on the right. A 235 rope' will bypass the last rappel.
